cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Kazakh Fact-Checking Benchmark"
message: "If you use this dataset or code, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  # TODO: replace with your full name before publishing to Zenodo
  - name: "Tim2190"
    alias: "Tim2190"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Tim2190/kazakh-factcheck-benchmark"
abstract: >-
  A pilot benchmark measuring how reliably large language models verify factual
  claims in the Kazakh language. 60 hand-built claims over three genres (legal,
  news, informal code-mixed dialogue), each faithful or deliberately distorted
  by a fixed taxonomy (number, entity, causal-relation, invented), with gold
  verdicts (SUPPORTED / REFUTED / NOT_ENOUGH_INFO). Five LLMs are run as
  open-book fact-checkers; every counted run is validated by a grounding gate.
keywords:
  - Kazakh
  - low-resource NLP
  - fact-checking
  - hallucination
  - large language models
  - benchmark
license: CC-BY-4.0
version: "1.0.0-pilot"
date-released: "2026-07-14"
